<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="179" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,980,1799]" box="[151,493,980,1007]" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,493,980,1007]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,493,980,1007]" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">
Is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Skogsberg" authorityYear="1939" box="[180,273,981,1007]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Copytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[180,273,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Copytus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a neocytherideid?
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,980,1799]" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">
<bibRefCitation author="Puri, H. S." box="[151,278,1016,1043]" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" pagination="902 - 914" refId="ref14892" refString="Puri, H. S. (1952) Ostracode genus Cytherideis and its allies. Journal of Paleontology, 26, 902 - 914." type="journal article" year="1952">Puri (1952)</bibRefCitation>
erected Cytherideisinae as new subfamily of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G.O.Sars" authorityYear="1925" box="[780,940,1017,1043]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cytherideidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cytherideidae</taxonomicName>
, based on the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Jones, 1856" authorityName=", Jones" authorityYear="1856" box="[1164,1432,1016,1043]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cushmanideidae" genus="Cytherideis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1164,1293,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Cytherideis</emphasis>
Jones, 1856
</taxonomicName>
, and joining also 
<taxonomicName authority="Skogsberg 1939" authorityName="Skogsberg" authorityYear="1939" box="[347,636,1053,1079]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Copytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[347,439,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Copytus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Skogsberg, T." box="[449,636,1053,1079]" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" pagination="415 - 425" refId="ref15084" refString="Skogsberg, T. (1939) A new genus and species of marine ostracods from South Georgia. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 23, 415 - 425." type="journal article" year="1939">Skogsberg 1939</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Dubovsky 1939" authorityName="Dubovsky" authorityYear="1939" box="[651,994,1053,1079]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cushmanideidae" genus="Pontocythere" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[651,799,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Pontocythere</emphasis>
Dubovsky 1939
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Brady, Crosskey &amp; Robertson 1874" authorityName="Brady, Crosskey &amp; Robertson" authorityYear="1874" class="Ostracoda" family="Krithidae" genus="Krithe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1008,1080,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Krithe</emphasis>
Brady, Crosskey &amp; Robertson 1874
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Blake 1933" authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1933" box="[223,520,1089,1115]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cushmanideidae" genus="Cushmanidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[223,377,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Cushmanidea</emphasis>
Blake 1933
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Puri 1952" authorityName="Puri" authorityYear="1952" box="[533,735,1088,1115]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideididae" genus="Sahnia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[533,611,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Sahnia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Puri, H. S." box="[620,735,1088,1115]" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" pagination="902 - 914" refId="ref14892" refString="Puri, H. S. (1952) Ostracode genus Cytherideis and its allies. Journal of Paleontology, 26, 902 - 914." type="journal article" year="1952">Puri 1952</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Puri 1952" authorityName="Puri" authorityYear="1952" box="[798,1090,1088,1115]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Neocytherideis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[798,966,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Neocytherideis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Puri, H. S." box="[975,1090,1088,1115]" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" pagination="902 - 914" refId="ref14892" refString="Puri, H. S. (1952) Ostracode genus Cytherideis and its allies. Journal of Paleontology, 26, 902 - 914." type="journal article" year="1952">Puri 1952</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sylvester-Bradley, P. C. &amp; Harding, J. P." pageId="2" pageNumber="179" pagination="753 - 755" refId="ref15242" refString="Sylvester-Bradley, P. C. &amp; Harding, J. P. (1953) The nomenclature of the ostracode genus Cytherideis. Journal of Paleontology, 27, 753 - 755." type="journal article" year="1953">Sylvester-Bradley &amp; Harding (1953)</bibRefCitation>
, based on a recommendation of the International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature, changed the name of this subfamily to Cytherideidinae. However, in the same publication, they considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Jones" authorityYear="1856" box="[1213,1342,1161,1187]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cushmanideidae" genus="Cytherideis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1213,1342,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Cytherideis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bosquet, 1852" authorityName="Bosquet" authorityYear="1852" box="[297,578,1196,1223]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Cypridea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[297,401,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Cypridea</emphasis>
Bosquet, 1852
</taxonomicName>
, a genus of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authority="Martin, 1940" authorityName="Martin" authorityYear="1940" box="[887,1186,1197,1223]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Cyprideinae">Cyprideinae Martin, 1940</taxonomicName>
. For that reason, 
<bibRefCitation author="Puri, H. S." pageId="2" pageNumber="179" pagination="305 - 306" refId="ref14918" refString="Puri, H. S. (1957) Notes on the ostracod subfamily Cytherideidinae Puri, 1952. Journal of the Washington Academy of Sciences, 47, 305 - 306." type="journal article" year="1957">Puri (1957)</bibRefCitation>
changed the name of the subfamily proposed by himself in 1952, to Neocytherideinae with 
<taxonomicName authority="Puri, 1952" authorityName="Puri" authorityYear="1952" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Neocytherideis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1268,1436,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Neocytherideis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Puri, H. S." box="[151,268,1268,1295]" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" pagination="902 - 914" refId="ref14892" refString="Puri, H. S. (1952) Ostracode genus Cytherideis and its allies. Journal of Paleontology, 26, 902 - 914." type="journal article" year="1952">Puri, 1952</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
being the nominate genus. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartmann, G. &amp; Puri, H. S." box="[579,857,1269,1295]" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" pagination="7 - 73" refId="ref13886" refString="Hartmann, G. &amp; Puri, H. S. (1974) Summary of Neontological and Paleontological Classification of Ostracoda. Mitteilungen aus dem hamburgischen zoologischen Museum und Institut, 70, 7 - 73." type="journal article" year="1974">Hartmann &amp; Puri (1974)</bibRefCitation>
raised this subfamily to full family status, which is considered appropriate for most ostracodologists.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="179" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,980,1799]" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">
<bibRefCitation author="Athersuch, J. &amp; Horne, D. J. &amp; Whittaker, J. E." box="[199,462,1341,1367]" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" refId="ref11787" refString="Athersuch, J., Horne, D. J. &amp; Whittaker, J. E. (1989) Marine and brackish water ostracods (superfamilies Cypridacea and Cytheracea). Keys and notes for the identification of the species. Synopsis of the British Fauna. New Series. 43. E. J. Brill, Leiden, 361 pp." type="book" year="1989">
Athersuch 
<emphasis box="[322,380,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">et al.</emphasis>
(1989)
</bibRefCitation>
presented a diagnosis for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Puri" authorityYear="1957" box="[760,960,1341,1367]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Neocytherideidae</taxonomicName>
, where the hinge is lophodont and the adductor scars composed of a somewhat oblique or curved row of four imprints. In fact, genera indisputably attributed to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Puri" authorityYear="1957" box="[180,380,1413,1439]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Neocytherideidae</taxonomicName>
, i.e., 
<taxonomicName authority="Puri, 1952" authorityName="Puri" authorityYear="1952" box="[440,735,1412,1439]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Neocytherideis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[440,608,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Neocytherideis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Puri, H. S." box="[615,735,1412,1439]" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" pagination="902 - 914" refId="ref14892" refString="Puri, H. S. (1952) Ostracode genus Cytherideis and its allies. Journal of Paleontology, 26, 902 - 914." type="journal article" year="1952">Puri, 1952</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruggieri, 1978" authorityName="Ruggieri" authorityYear="1978" box="[747,1089,1413,1439]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideididae" genus="Procytherideis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[747,911,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Procytherideis</emphasis>
Ruggieri, 1978
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Athersuch, 1982" authorityName="Athersuch" authorityYear="1982" box="[1100,1436,1413,1439]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideididae" genus="Sahnicythere" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1100,1245,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Sahnicythere</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Athersuch, J." box="[1251,1436,1413,1439]" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" pagination="231 - 275" refId="ref11729" refString="Athersuch, J. (1982) Some ostracod genera formerly of the family Cytherideidae Sars. In: Bate, R. H., Robinson, E. &amp; Sheppard, L. M. (Eds.), Fossil and Recent Ostracods. Ellis Horwood, Hertfordshire, pp. 231 - 275." type="book chapter" year="1982">Athersuch, 1982</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(for 
<taxonomicName authority="Puri, 1952" authorityName="Puri" authorityYear="1952" box="[202,409,1448,1475]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideididae" genus="Sahnia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[202,280,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Sahnia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Puri, H. S." box="[289,409,1448,1475]" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" pagination="902 - 914" refId="ref14892" refString="Puri, H. S. (1952) Ostracode genus Cytherideis and its allies. Journal of Paleontology, 26, 902 - 914." type="journal article" year="1952">Puri, 1952</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Whatley, Chadwick, Coxill &amp; Toy, 1987" authorityName="Whatley, Chadwick, Coxill &amp; Toy" authorityYear="1987" box="[475,1137,1449,1475]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideididae" genus="Papillosacythere" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[475,664,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Papillosacythere</emphasis>
Whatley, Chadwick, Coxill &amp; Toy, 1987
</taxonomicName>
, show hinge and adductor scars in accordance to 
<bibRefCitation author="Athersuch, J. &amp; Horne, D. J. &amp; Whittaker, J. E." box="[411,680,1485,1511]" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" refId="ref11787" refString="Athersuch, J., Horne, D. J. &amp; Whittaker, J. E. (1989) Marine and brackish water ostracods (superfamilies Cypridacea and Cytheracea). Keys and notes for the identification of the species. Synopsis of the British Fauna. New Series. 43. E. J. Brill, Leiden, 361 pp." type="book" year="1989">
Athersuch 
<emphasis box="[535,594,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">et al.</emphasis>
(1989)
</bibRefCitation>
. The appendages of this family, as also described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Athersuch, J. &amp; Horne, D. J. &amp; Whittaker, J. E." pageId="2" pageNumber="179" refId="ref11787" refString="Athersuch, J., Horne, D. J. &amp; Whittaker, J. E. (1989) Marine and brackish water ostracods (superfamilies Cypridacea and Cytheracea). Keys and notes for the identification of the species. Synopsis of the British Fauna. New Series. 43. E. J. Brill, Leiden, 361 pp." type="book" year="1989">
Athersuch 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">et al.</emphasis>
(1989)
</bibRefCitation>
, are similar in all genera. The hemipenis morphology, especially the distal process shape, varies among species of the same genus. This is the reason why they did not consider soft parts in the generic taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Puri" authorityYear="1957" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Neocytherideidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,980,1799]" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Skogsberg" authorityYear="1939" box="[199,291,1629,1655]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Copytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,291,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Copytus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, besides other minor differences, has (i) a proportionally longer hinge line, not confined to the posterior half of the length, as typical of most species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Puri" authorityYear="1957" box="[686,886,1665,1691]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Neocytherideidae</taxonomicName>
, and (ii) bears a small rounded group of four adductor scars, which differ from the somewhat oblique or curved vertical row of the neocytherideids. We understand that the hinge and central muscle scars of this genus distinguish it from all other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Puri" authorityYear="1957" box="[1056,1256,1737,1763]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Neocytherideidae</taxonomicName>
, and therefore a new family is herein proposed to hold the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Skogsberg" authorityYear="1939" box="[742,834,1773,1799]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Copytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[742,834,1773,1799]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Copytus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see chapter ‘Taxonomy’).
</paragraph>
